The paper deals with the problem of multi-robot coordinated planning, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of a planner that ensures safe paths and adherence to kinematic constraints, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a new algorithm that achieves a trade-off between computational time and solution quality, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.MA) and optimization (cs.LG).
